In order to run a successful business, you have to take care of YOU!🤍
Happy Friyay! Welcome back to this brow client + brow videos 😅 #browshaping at it’s finest 💫

I consider myself lucky to have access to a gym that enables me to blend my work commitments with my social interactions, all while maintaining a healthy and consistent fitness routine. This time I got to bring my gal with me 🤍 I often get asked how I manage to have a little bit of balance, I think this describes it perfectly. ✨

Taking care of your clients, is taking care of your business. I want to share a client review that will put into perspective why these little things go a long way: 

ELIZABETH GONZALEZ
05/08/2023
NEW CLIENT BROW WAX with Cindy Aguilar

“I had a great experience with Cindy! I drove from San Diego, and due to traffic, I realized I would be arriving 10 minutes late, so I sent her a message to let her know. She was easy to reach and communicated effectively, and even sent me a picture of the location because I was having a bit of a hard time finding it. Once I arrived, she was very considerate and offered me snacks and water and made me feel welcomed!
One of my brows is a little thinner than the other, so she asked about my eyebrow history and asked what I wanted to be done during my visit. She took the time to make them look as even as possible, and the process was not painful at all!” 

LA is the definition of traffic and staying busy. Most of my clients travel from far, or are just getting out work/catching a break. Often time, they tend to use their lunch time to get an appointment. I’m always so appreciative for your support 🤍 Always feel free to grab something on the go!
Step by Step: Brow Lamination 🤍 A service I most enjoy doing. 💌

Let’s talk BROW FILL IN: 
Step 1: Use Highlighter - this helps you have a visual representation of where you can start shading. It doesn’t have to be perfect at first, remember this is suppose to help you initiate. For a creamier result, you can use a little bit of cortisone onto your brush. 

Step 2: Brow Pencil - I personally find this easier among my clients. I also advise using powder for a natural look, and for oily skin. 

Step 3: Clear Brow Gel - This allows the hairs to stay in place and gives more volume. As I mentioned in the video, a good trick to get a “Fluffy/Messy” but tamed look, is brushing the inner brows the opposite direction. 

I hope this helps you 💞
